title: Insufficient storage space warning
answer:
For phones that support external microSD cards, if you have a card in your phone, it is recommended that you move photos, music, videos and other files from the phone's internal storage to the microSD card. 

 Clear storage space. 

 If your phone has Phone Manager preloaded, open Phone Manager, select Phone accelerator > Storage cleaner and then follow the on-screen prompts to clear storage space. 

 If you still receive the insufficient storage warning after attempting the preceding steps, it is recommended that you back up any important data and then restore factory settings.
keywords: insufficient memory, insufficient, not enough memory, clean memory
